Questions:
Which of the following is considered an experimental procedure in the COH Protocol# 20717 study?
A) Standard post-operative care and follow-up with your primary care physician;
B) Use of a Vivofit 4 watch to track daily steps and report health data via a study-provided tablet;
C) Routine blood tests and physical examinations conducted during hospital stays;
D) Regularly scheduled clinic visits for standard post-surgical monitoring.

Correct answer: B

If you decide not to participate in the Perioperative Telemonitoring to Optimize Cancer Care and Outcomes study, what is the alternative option available to you?
A) You will be required to participate in a different research study; 
B) You will not receive any surgical treatment for your cancer;
C) You will receive standard post-surgical care without the additional telemonitoring program;
D) You will be discharged without any follow-up care or instructions.

Correct answer: C
